<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles.css" />
    <script src="/static/theme.js" defer></script>
    <script src="/static/app.js" defer></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="layout">
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <a class="brand" href="/">
          <span class="moon-logo brand-logo" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="moon-logo-ring"></span>
            <span class="moon-logo-core"></span>
            <span class="moon-logo-orbit moon-logo-orbit-one"></span>
            <span class="moon-logo-orbit moon-logo-orbit-two"></span>
          </span>
          <span class="brand-copy">
            <strong>MOON Control</strong>
            <span>Voice command system</span>
          </span>
        </a>

        <div class="sidebar-section">
          <p class="sidebar-label">Overview</p>
          <nav class="sidebar-nav">
            <a class="nav-item active" href="/">Home</a>
            <% if (currentUser) { %>
              <a class="nav-item" href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
            <% } %>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <main class="main">
        <header class="topbar">
          <div>
            <h1 class="page-title">MOON</h1>
            <div class="meta">Deterministic voice control for Discord servers.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="actions">
            <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" data-theme-toggle>
              Theme: <span data-theme-label>Light</span>
            </button>
            <% if (currentUser) { %>
              <a class="button" href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
              <a class="button primary" href="/logout">Log Out</a>
            <% } else { %>
              <a class="button primary" href="/login">Log In With Discord</a>
            <% } %>
          </div>
        </header>

        <% if (typeof error !== "undefined" && error) { %>
          <div class="notice error"><%= error %></div>
        <% } %>

        <section class="landing-hero">
          <article class="card landing-panel landing-copy">
            <div class="card-body">
              <div class="badge-row landing-badges">
                <span class="eyebrow">MOON Voice Control</span>
                <span class="badge live">Deterministic commands</span>
                <span class="badge">Groq Whisper STT</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="headline">A fast voice-command system for Discord that stays predictable under pressure.</h2>
              <p class="section-lead landing-lead">
                MOON turns short spoken commands into reliable moderation actions without fuzzy AI intent
                guessing. Admins decide exactly who can speak, which actions are allowed, and how each guild
                should behave.
              </p>
              <div class="inline-actions landing-actions">
                <% if (loggedIn) { %>
                  <a class="button primary" href="/dashboard">Open Dashboard</a>
                <% } else { %>
                  <a class="button primary" href="/login">Connect Discord</a>
                <% } %>
                <a class="button" href="#command-system">See How It Works</a>
              </div>
              <div class="landing-stat-row">
                <div class="landing-stat">
                  <strong>Shared command set</strong>
                  <span>Short global commands users can learn once and repeat anywhere.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-stat">
                  <strong>Per-guild controls</strong>
                  <span>Wake word, access rules, and action toggles stay in your dashboard.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-stat">
                  <strong>Live moderation</strong>
                  <span>Move, mute, disconnect, lock, and role-manage without typing mid-game.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <aside class="card landing-panel landing-visual-shell">
            <div class="card-body landing-visual">
              <div class="landing-orbit">
                <span class="moon-logo hero-logo" aria-hidden="true">
                  <span class="moon-logo-ring"></span>
                  <span class="moon-logo-core"></span>
                  <span class="moon-logo-orbit moon-logo-orbit-one"></span>
                  <span class="moon-logo-orbit moon-logo-orbit-two"></span>
                </span>
                <div class="landing-orbit-glow"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="landing-command-stack">
                <div class="landing-command-chip">moon lock vc</div>
                <div class="landing-command-chip">moon mute me</div>
                <div class="landing-command-chip">moon drag aditya here</div>
                <div class="landing-command-chip">moon disconnect all</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </section>

        <section class="landing-grid" id="command-system">
          <article class="card">
            <div class="card-body stack">
              <div>
                <span class="eyebrow">Why it works</span>
                <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 10px;">Built for noisy real-time voice channels</h2>
                <p class="section-lead">
                  MOON keeps the command system short and repeatable, then matches the transcript against a
                  fixed command list instead of trying to understand free-form speech.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="quick-grid">
                <div class="quick-item">
                  <strong>Transcribe</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Groq Whisper Large v3 converts voice to text.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quick-item">
                  <strong>Match</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Deterministic similarity matching chooses only known commands.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quick-item">
                  <strong>Resolve</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Users, channels, and roles are matched against live guild data.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quick-item">
                  <strong>Execute</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Discord actions run in a safe, predictable order.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <div class="card-body stack">
              <div>
                <span class="eyebrow">What admins control</span>
                <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 10px;">Everything that matters stays in your hands</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="landing-list">
                <div class="landing-list-item">
                  <strong>Access rules</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Allow commands by Discord admin, user ID, or role ID.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-list-item">
                  <strong>Voice behavior</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Set wake word, silence cutoff, cooldown, and transcript visibility.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-list-item">
                  <strong>Command safety</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Toggle drag, mute, disconnect, and lock actions per guild.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-list-item">
                  <strong>Deterministic learning</strong>
                  <span class="muted">Users see the same command catalog in Discord and on the website.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </section>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

